  <main>
    <div class="calc-page">

      <div class="calc-page-header">
        <div class="page-eyebrow">
          <svg width="12" height="12" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5"><path d="M14 2H6a2 2 0 00-2 2v16a2 2 0 002 2h12a2 2 0 002-2V8z"/><polyline points="14 2 14 8 20 8"/></svg>
          Freelance and Contractor Tax
        </div>
        <h1>Self-Employment Tax Calculator</h1>
        <p>Estimate Social Security and Medicare taxes for 2025 freelance, contractor, gig, or small business income. Includes deductible half and quarterly payment estimate.</p>
      </div>

      <% if (result) { %>
      <div class="result-card">
        <div class="result-card-header">
          <div class="result-icon">
            <svg width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#fff" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M14 2H6a2 2 0 00-2 2v16a2 2 0 002 2h12a2 2 0 002-2V8z"/><polyline points="14 2 14 8 20 8"/></svg>
          </div>
          <h2>Your Self-Employment Tax Estimate</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="result-primary">
          <span class="result-label">Total Self-Employment Tax</span>
          <span class="result-amount">$<%= Math.round(result.totalSelfEmploymentTax).toLocaleString() %></span>
        </div>
        <div class="result-grid">
          <div class="result-item">
            <div class="ri-label">Net Profit</div>
            <div class="ri-value">$<%= Math.round(result.netProfit).toLocaleString() %></div>
          </div>
          <div class="result-item">
            <div class="ri-label">SE Taxable Income (92.35%)</div>
            <div class="ri-value">$<%= Math.round(result.seTaxableIncome).toLocaleString() %></div>
          </div>
          <div class="result-item">
            <div class="ri-label">Social Security Portion (12.4%)</div>
            <div class="ri-value red">$<%= Math.round(result.socialSecurityTax).toLocaleString() %></div>
          </div>
          <div class="result-item">
            <div class="ri-label">Medicare Portion (2.9%)</div>
            <div class="ri-value red">$<%= Math.round(result.medicareTax).toLocaleString() %></div>
          </div>
          <div class="result-item">
            <div class="ri-label">Deductible Half of SE Tax</div>
            <div class="ri-value green">$<%= Math.round(result.deductibleHalf).toLocaleString() %></div>
          </div>
          <div class="result-item">
            <div class="ri-label">Est. Quarterly Payment</div>
            <div class="ri-value">$<%= Math.round(result.estimatedQuarterlyPayment).toLocaleString() %></div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="ad-zone">
        <div class="ad-zone-label">Advertisement</div>
        <ins class="adsbygoogle" style="display:block"
          data-ad-client="ca-pub-5193834725888549"
          data-ad-slot="5205436277"
          data-ad-format="auto"
          data-full-width-responsive="true"></ins>
        <script>(adsbygoogle = window.adsbygoogle || []).push({});</script>
      </div>
      <% } %>

      <div class="calc-card-form">
        <h2>Enter Your Income Information</h2>
        <form method="POST" action="/self-employment-tax-calculator">
          <div class="form-grid">
            <div class="form-field">
              <label for="taxYear">Tax Year</label>
              <select id="taxYear" name="taxYear">
                <option value="2025" <%= (!form.taxYear || form.taxYear === '2025') ? 'selected' : '' %>>2025</option>
                <option value="2026" <%= form.taxYear === '2026' ? 'selected' : '' %>>2026</option>
              </select>
            </div>
            <div class="form-field">
              <label for="grossIncome">Gross Self-Employment Income</label>
              <div class="input-wrap"><span class="input-prefix">$</span>
                <input type="number" id="grossIncome" name="grossIncome" min="0" step="any" value="<%= form.grossIncome || '' %>" placeholder="75000" required>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="form-field full">
              <label for="businessExpenses">Business Expenses</label>
              <div class="input-wrap"><span class="input-prefix">$</span>
                <input type="number" id="businessExpenses" name="businessExpenses" min="0" step="any" value="<%= form.businessExpenses || '' %>" placeholder="15000">
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="form-actions">
            <button type="submit" class="btn-calc">
              <svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M14 2H6a2 2 0 00-2 2v16a2 2 0 002 2h12a2 2 0 002-2V8z"/><polyline points="14 2 14 8 20 8"/></svg>
              Calculate Self-Employment Tax
            </button>
          </div>
        </form>
      </div>

      <div class="hiw-section">
        <div class="section-eyebrow">How It Works</div>
        <h2>How Self-Employment Tax Is Calculated</h2>
        <p>When you work for yourself, you pay both the employee and employer share of FICA taxes. Here is the exact calculation chain.</p>
        <div class="hiw-steps">
          <div class="hiw-step">
            <div class="hiw-step-num">1</div>
            <div class="hiw-step-body">
              <h3>Calculate Net Profit</h3>
              <p>Subtract your deductible business expenses from gross self-employment income to find net profit. This is your starting point for SE tax.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="hiw-step">
            <div class="hiw-step-num">2</div>
            <div class="hiw-step-body">
              <h3>Apply the 92.35% Rule</h3>
              <p>The IRS allows you to reduce net profit by 7.65% before applying SE tax rates. This accounts for the employer-equivalent portion you are effectively deducting. The result is your SE taxable income.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="hiw-step">
            <div class="hiw-step-num">3</div>
            <div class="hiw-step-body">
              <h3>Apply SE Tax Rates</h3>
              <p>Social Security tax is 12.4% on SE taxable income up to the annual wage base. Medicare tax is 2.9% on all SE taxable income with no limit. Together these form the 15.3% SE tax rate.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="hiw-step">
            <div class="hiw-step-num">4</div>
            <div class="hiw-step-body">
              <h3>Deductible Half Reduces Income Tax</h3>
              <p>You can deduct half of your SE tax when calculating your adjusted gross income on your federal return. This partially offsets the burden of paying both sides of FICA.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="formula-box">
          <div class="formula-box-label">Formula Reference</div>
          <code><span class="comment">// Step 1 - Net Profit</span>
<span class="highlight">Net Profit</span>         = Gross Income - Business Expenses

<span class="comment">// Step 2 - SE Taxable Income</span>
<span class="highlight">SE Taxable Income</span>  = Net Profit x 0.9235

<span class="comment">// Step 3 - SE Tax (2025 rates)</span>
<span class="highlight">Social Security</span>    = SE Taxable Income x 12.4%  (up to $176,100)
<span class="highlight">Medicare</span>           = SE Taxable Income x 2.9%
<span class="highlight">Total SE Tax</span>       = Social Security + Medicare

<span class="comment">// Step 4 - Deductible Half</span>
<span class="highlight">Deductible Half</span>    = Total SE Tax x 0.50</code>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="ad-zone">
        <div class="ad-zone-label">Advertisement</div>
        <ins class="adsbygoogle" style="display:block"
          data-ad-client="ca-pub-5193834725888549"
          data-ad-slot="4212978293"
          data-ad-format="auto"
          data-full-width-responsive="true"></ins>
        <script>(adsbygoogle = window.adsbygoogle || []).push({});</script>
